divs: Sighting DetailsNot sure if anyone is interested, but I found what "appeared to be a silver disc shaped object in the sky in a photo from 2007. I was looking for a business on google maps and while viewing the photo of the street, I tried zooming for a better view and accidently ended up looking at the sky, where I saw the "object". It doesn't appear to be a reflection since a part of it is clearly behind a small cloud. Did not look like any aircraft I'm familiar with. A very curious thing. In case anyone would like to take a look, the address I googled was 3128 Forest Lane, Dallas, TX. I then changed the view to look at the businesses across the street (toward Burlington Coat Factory) and that is where I saw the object in the sky.
Summary: Silver Disc shaped object in photo on Google maps
